From Daniel M Silevitch Subject Re Word for Windows Problems In article Jason Cleeve writes In trying to use the Equation editor in Word for Windows I get a couple of error messages along the lines of Can't find font MT Extra for default Some characters my not be displayed or installing Equation editor again or reinstall a new Similar for the font I know I have these fonts on my system but are unable to use I have tried both of these solutions to no If anyone has had similar problems and has found a way to fix this could they let me It is urgently required Thanks IT'S BACK Congratulations you've just discovered a very nasty and very frequently ecountered bug in the Word Setup Once you know what is wrong it is quite easy to Go into the Fonts dialog under Control Panel and select the two fonts MT Extra and Delete them but only delete the list entries not the disk Now select Add and add the fonts MT Extra Plain and Fences Close the Font box close Control Panel and restart Everything should be alright Does anyone know if Microsoft has fixed this thing yet They HAVE to know about it by now it's been so frequently Daniel Silevitch Massachusetts Institute of Technology